But these statements only mean that dolus and culpa are often undjstinguishable by a court of law. The phenomena of gross negligence are precisely similar to those of dishonest intention, and it is often impossible for a court to decide which interpretation they ought to bear. Again, as the consequences are equally mischievous, there is no reason why they should not be subject to the same legal sanction.
